rk (short for regex kitchen) is a an interactive tool intended to make the task
of crafting regexes a little less painful. This is my first curses project, and
I have tried to keep the interface separate from the logic so that I can use the
same code if I ever decide to pick up GTK+.

rk's design goal is to be somewhat like a fast food restaurant - get in, do what
you have to, and get out with what you came for as quickly and painlessly as
possible. Since its intended workflow does not leave it running when it is not
in active use, I am not especially interested in being 'lightweight': if a
little more RAM greases the wheels or makes us more responsive, it's probably a
good trade here.

